decompress_special(25.10)                            decompress_special(25.10)

Name
       decompress_special  -  Decompresses  Power-Grid (PG) objects within the
       specified area, layer, or net

Syntax
       decompress_special

       [-help]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}]

       [-layers <layer>+]

       [-nets <net>+]

       Decompresses Power-Grid (PG) objects within the specified area,  layer,
       or  net.  This command decompresses only the overlapped part in case of
       partial overlapping. The rest of the part is regrouped.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information  for  each  decompress_special  parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all  its  parameters,  use
              the man command:

              man decompress_special

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the coordinates for the area from which PG needs to be
              decompressed.  The  decompress_special command decompresses only
              those special wires and special vias,  which  exist  within  the
              area specified by this parameter.

              Default: All PG structures are decompressed.

       -layers <layer>+
              Specifies  the  layers on which PG decompression is needed. This
              parameter requires either LEF layer names or a routing layer in-
              dex value (for example, 1 for the first routing  layer,   2  for
              the second routing layer, and so on).

       -nets <net>+
              Specifies the nets from which PG decompression is needed.

Example
       The  following  command  decompresses  %s  special_wires  and  %s  spe-
       cial_vias:

       decompress_special -area {100 100 120 120} -layer Via56

